The [[NewtonKeyboard]] allows a user to add information to your Newton by typing as well has writing.  Most keyboards have a standard Macintosh Serial port and will require a Dongle (see [[AboutDongles]]) or [SER-001] board.

#  Inside the keyboard
(Any one care to fill this out more?  I've taken the first step.  --Puckdropper)

The serial cable connects to a header on a circuit board.  It is wired as such:

# Keyboard to printed circuit board layout
* DIN 8    Color
* 1  Tan
* 2  Tan
* 3  No Connection
* 4  Black (small)
* 5  White
* 6  No Connection
* 7  Red
* 8  Green
* Outside Black (large)


